    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Throttle Body Cleaning"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "461_3.0_jpn_11291969_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Soak a paper rag with carburetor cleaner and wipe off any dirt (carbon, etc.) on the inside of the throttle bore and throttle valve end faces."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Be sure to remove the throttle body before starting work.",
        "Do not clean the throttle valve bearing (A) to protect the molybdenum coating.",
        "Use the stock carburetor cleaner.",
        "Do not inject carburetor cleaner directly into the throttle body."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Throttle Body Mounting"
    },
